ker RP</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0300-5127</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>545c972cb0f158.34561993</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>1B2910F3-6A4F-4110-9B1F-A289A9E8F4C2</gtr:id><gtr:title>DNA uracil repair initiated by the archaeal ExoIII homologue Mth212 via direct strand incision.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Nucleic acids research</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/51995c2ab8035a0f674f6212605e8167"><gtr:id>51995c2ab8035a0f674f6212605e8167</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Schomacher L</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2009-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0305-1048</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>545c9328562043.51739242</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>BBC6FEF8-056E-4D7B-B4DF-E6EE24DBD2BD</gtr:id><gtr:title>An archaeal order with multiple minichromosome maintenance genes.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Microbiology (Reading, England)</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/3a52265e8f578e0316d1fb39ccbaf622"><gtr:id>3a52265e8f578e0316d1fb39ccbaf622</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Walters AD</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1350-0872</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>545c9328ca6449.79678418</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>D207DC3D-8D77-4B30-8893-4627302036EE</gtr:id><gtr:title>Shuttle vector system for Methanococcus maripaludis with improved transformation efficiency.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Applied and environmental microbiology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/3a52265e8f578e0316d1fb39ccbaf622"><gtr:id>3a52265e8f578e0316d1fb39ccbaf622</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Walters AD</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0099-2240</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>545c972d053820.54516992</gtr:outcomeId></